author: Brian Farmer
title: Watch 2 Chainz and Gucci Mane Take Over Jimmy Fallon With Epic Performance of “Good Drank”
text:
After dropping the record back in October, 2 Chainz and Gucci Mane have been reaping the benefits of their trap hit “Good Drank.” Following the release of the track’s official music video earlier last month, the rappers ventured to Jimmy Fallon’s Tonight Show to put on one of the more epic late night performances.
Backed by the Fonzworth Bentley Trap Choir and the legendary Mike Dean, 2 Chainz and Gucci have set the bar for all future late night live trap performances. In addition to the phenomenal performance, the two joined Keri Russel and Aaron Paul for a hilarious edition of “Password.”
Check out the live performance above and watch the two rappers go head-to-head in “Password” below.
